caption:
Table 1. Results of 1-way 1-shot and 1-way 5-shot segmentation on the FSS-1000 data 
set employing the mean Intersection Over Union (mIoU) metric. Best results in bold.

Table 2. Results of 1-way 1-shot and 1-way 5-shot segmentation on PASCAL-5 i data 
set employing the mean Intersection-Over-Union (mIoU) metric. Best results for each 
backbone architecture are highlighted in bold. We employ ? to denote the difference 
between 1-and 5-shot settings.

Table 3. Results of 1-way 1-shot segmentation on the FSS-1000 dataset with different 
fusion strategies to combine multiple scale-space representations. Best results in bold.

Table 4. Full supervision vs weak-supervision performance in the 1-shot scenario. Type 
of supervision in brackets.

Table 2. Effect of combining different level feature maps in the encoder network. Best 
result is highlighted in bold.

Table 3. Parameter complexity in different approaches and their performance (mIoU) 
on 1-shot segmentation on PASCAL-5 i . Methods are ordered based on number of learn-
able parameters.

Table 4. Results of 1-way 1-shot and 5-shot segmentation on COCO-20 i data set 
employing the mean Intersection Over Union (mIoU) metric. Methods are divided 
according to the backbone used.
